<help-screen version="1">
    <thumbnail>
        <script>
            <block s="reportAskFor">
                <l/>
                <block s="reifyReporter">
                    <script/>
                    <list/>
                </block>
                <list/>
            </block>
        </script>
    </thumbnail>
    <box color="gray">
        <column>
            <p>Ask another object a question.</p>
            <p>Ask a particular sprite where it is:</p>
            <diagram>
                <script>
                    <block s="reportAskFor" bubble="1">
                        <l>Sprite(3)</l>
                        <block s="reifyReporter">
                            <autolambda>
                                <block s="reportNewList">
                                    <list>
                                        <block s="xPosition"/>
                                        <block s="yPosition"/>
                                    </list>
                                </block>
                            </autolambda>
                            <list/>
                        </block>
                        <list/>
                    </block>
                </script>
                <bubbles>
                    <img src="reportAskFor_list1.png" width="80" height="69"/>
                </bubbles>
            </diagram>
            <p>Ask all sprites except myself where they are:</p>
            <diagram>
                <script scale="0.9">
                    <block s="reportMap" bubble="1">
                        <block s="reifyReporter">
                            <autolambda>
                                <block s="reportAskFor">
                                    <l highlight="true"/>
                                    <block s="reifyReporter">
                                        <autolambda>
                                            <block s="reportNewList">
                                                <list>
                                                    <block s="xPosition"/>
                                                    <block s="yPosition"/>
                                                </list>
                                            </block>
                                        </autolambda>
                                        <list/>
                                    </block>
                                    <list/>
                                </block>
                            </autolambda>
                            <list/>
                        </block>
                        <block s="reportGet">
                            <l><option>other sprites</option></l>
                        </block>
                    </block>
                </script>
                <bubbles>
                    <img src="reportAskFor_list2.png" width="129" height="52"/>
                </bubbles>
            </diagram>
            <p>
                (Each sprite is used, one at a time, to fill the empty slot
                circled in green.)
            </p>
        </column>
    </box>
    <box color="blue">
        <column>
            <p>
                The expression is evaluated in the environment of the other
                object, so it usees that object's local variables and methods. If
                you want to use one of the sender's variables inside the script,
                leave an empty input slot in the script, click the right
                arrowhead at the end of the ASK, and use the sender's variable as
                input to ASK.
            </p>
            <diagram>
                <script>
                    <block s="reportAskFor">
                        <l>Sprite(3)</l>
                        <block s="reifyReporter">
                            <autolambda>
                                <block s="reportNewList">
                                    <list>
                                        <l arrow-end="1"/>
                                        <block var="its variable"/>
                                    </list>
                                </block>
                            </autolambda>
                            <list/>
                        </block>
                        <list>
                            <block var="my variable" arrow-start="1" arrow-detour="20"/>
                        </list>
                    </block>
                </script>
            </diagram>
            <p>
                In this example, “its variable” is defined in Sprite(3), so
                it can be used inside the expression. “My variable” is
                defined in the asking sprite, so it can't be used inside the
                expression. Instead it is used as input to ASK, which fills
                the empty slot in the LIST block with it.
            </p>
        </column>
    </box>
</help-screen>
